Join the Conversation To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs Prep roundup: Donnay leads EV-W/K to CMC title TIMES STAFF REPORT 10:25 p.m. CDT October 22, 2015 Sports brief (Photo: Times graphic) 
PIERZ — Anna Donnay won the girls race in a time of 18:28.33 to lead Eden Valley-Watkins/Kimball to the team title at the Central Minnesota Conference prep cross country meet held Thursday afternoon at the Pierz Golf Course. 
Ali Ruprecht finished fourth in a time of 20:02.42 to lead Holdingford to a second-place finish. 
The Huskers won the boys team title led by Marcus Rick and Luke Ryan, who finished sixth (17:25.08) and seventh (17:52.36). 
Connor Schank of Howard Lake-Waverly/Winsted won the boys race in a time of 16:02.99. Ben Borash of Royalton finished second in a time of 16:59.05. 
Boys 
Team scores — 1. Holdingford 55; 2. Maple Lake 71; 3. Osakis 94; 4. Howard Lake-Waverly/Winsted 103; 5. Royalton 108; 6. Pierz 151; 7. St. John’s Prep 163; 8. Paynesville 174; 9. Eden Valley-Watkins/Kimball 189. 
Girls 
Team scores — 1. Eden Valley-Watkins/Kimball 55; 2. Holdingford 58; 3. Maple Lake 59; 4. Osakis 106; 5. Howard Lake-Waverly/Winsted 107; 6. St. John’s Prep 163; 7. Paynesville 169; 8. Royalton 213. 
Girls swimming 
LITTLE FALLS 104, BECKER 77 
LITTLE FALLS — Makyla Klever won the girls 50 (27.00) and 100 (1:06.78) freestyle to lead Little Falls past Becker in a Granite Ridge Conference dual meet. 
Annie Corbett won the 200 (2:16.27) and 500 (5:47.47) freestyle. 
ALBANY 52, MILACA 50 
ALBANY — Freshman Kallie Linn won both the 200 freestyle (2:09. 67) and the 500 freestyle (5:50.25) to lead the Huskies past Milaca in Granite Ridge Conference action. 
Alisha Ritter also highlighted the Huskies with a win in the 100 butterfly (1:10.16). Breanna Mehrwerth won both the 50 free (26.51) and the 100 free (59.63) to lead the Wolves.
